HEADWORD: Lopping
<hw>Lop"ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A cutting off, as of
branches; that which is cut off; leavings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>loppings</qex> made from that stock whilst it stood.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loppy</ent>⟦br⟧
